  "text": "The Kafka consumer offset commit flow travels through a multi-stage pipeline from the client to the broker and finally to the __consumer_offsets topic.\n\nOn the Client Side:\n1. KafkaConsumer.commitSync() (line 940) delegates to a ConsumerDelegate implementation\n2. ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync() (line 741) calls coordinator.commitOffsetsSync() to send the offsets\n3. ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync() (line 1140) orchestrates the commit, calling sendOffsetCommitRequest(offsets) (line 1155)\n4. ConsumerCoordinator.sendOffsetCommitRequest() (line 1270) constructs an OffsetCommit request and sends it to the group coordinator broker via client.send()\n\nOn the Broker/Group Coordinator Side:\n5. GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets() (line 1971) receives the request and schedules a write operation via runtime.scheduleWriteOperation()\n6. GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset() (line 852) is invoked by the scheduled operation and delegates to offsetMetadataManager.commitOffset()\n7. OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset() (line 600) validates the request and creates CoordinatorRecord objects for each partition offset by calling GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord() (line 650)\n8. GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord() (line 467) creates a CoordinatorRecord wrapping OffsetCommitKey and OffsetCommitValue objects\n\nLog Append and Offset Storage:\n9. CoordinatorRuntime.scheduleWriteOperation() (line 2182) enqueues a CoordinatorWriteEvent\n10. CoordinatorRuntime.CoordinatorWriteEvent.run() (line 1394) executes the operation and calls context.append() (line 1402)\n11. CoordinatorRuntime.CoordinatorContext.append() (line 948) appends the records to a memory batch builder at line 1059, then calls maybeFlushCurrentBatch() at line 1084\n12. CoordinatorRuntime.CoordinatorContext.flushCurrentBatch() (line 779) calls partitionWriter.append() (line 795) to write the batch to the underlying log partition\n13. The PartitionWriter.append() method writes the MemoryRecords containing the offset commit data to the __consumer_offsets topic partition, where they are persisted and replicated\n\nThe offset commit records are serialized as OffsetCommitKey/OffsetCommitValue pairs in the log, allowing consumers to fetch their committed offsets on restart or rebalance."
}

